        <num>CCP 3404</num>
        <heading>3404.  Priority in appointment</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3404.  Priority in appointment
When a succession representative has been appointed by a court of the decedent's domicile outside Louisiana, priority shall be given to him in the appointment of a representative in Louisiana, unless he is disqualified under Article 3097.  Otherwise, priority shall be given in the appointment of a representative as provided in Article 3098.</p>
        </content>
